OL,3,CFewer women would prefer to switch
OL,4,Cgender than they once did, study shows
OL,6,FFar fewer women today would prefer to
OL,7,Fswitch gender than they once did,
OL,8,Faccording to a study.
OL,10,FResearchers compared public attitudes
OL,11,Fand behaviours in the 1930s and 1940s
OL,12,Fwith those in 2024 to find out how
OL,13,Fsociety had changed over the course of
OL,14,Falmost a century.
OL,16,FThey found that 37% of women in 1947
OL,17,Fsaid they would rather be a man, with
OL,18,Fjust 9% feeling the same way today.
