OL,6,FThe team behind the study said the
OL,7,Fresults were a sign of the progress
OL,8,Fmade on women's rights and equality in
OL,9,Fthe UK.
OL,11,FMen's preferences remain the same,
OL,12,Fhowever ` around one in 20 (5%) said
OL,13,Fthey would rather be a woman today,
OL,14,Falmost the same figure as in the 1940s
OL,15,F(4%), the study said.
