OL,6,FA quarter of men in 1947 said they did
OL,7,Fno housework, with only 4% of men
OL,8,Fadmitting to this today.
OL,10,FHowever, women still do the bulk of
OL,11,Fthe chores ` according to the Office
OL,12,Ffor National Statistics (ONS), women
OL,13,Fspend around three and half hours a
OL,14,Fday doing unpaid work activities such
OL,15,Fas housework and volunteering, almost
OL,16,Fan hour more than the average man.
OL,18,FThe study also found that while people
OL,19,Fused to value job security over high
OL,20,Fwages, opinion today is much more
OL,21,Fclosely divided.
