OL,6,FSome 73% of people in 1946 said job
OL,7,Fsecurity was more important, but that
OL,8,Ffigure is only 41% today, with 46% of
OL,9,FBrits prioritising the highest
OL,10,Fpossible wages.
OL,12,FRegarding education, only 21% of
OL,13,Fpeople in 1937 thought children should
OL,14,Fhave homework ` that figure is now 68%.
OL,16,FWhile Britain used to be split on
OL,17,Fwhether boys and girls should be
OL,18,Ftaught separately (43%) or together
OL,19,F(45%), people are now hugely in favour
OL,20,Fof them being taught together, with
OL,21,Fthis figure at 76%, the study found.
